cate safely and covertly in hostile environments. Whether you are a privacy\n  advocate, a dissident, or a sleeper agent, you are equally likely to find Liberté\n  Linux useful as a mission-critical communication aid. \'\nurl: http://dee.su/liberte\nsource_url: https://github.com/mkdesu/liberte\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://github.com/mkdesu/liberte/blob/master/README.md\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Security-focused_operating_system#Libert.C3.A9_Linux.5B7.5D\n','2013-10-29 13:50:01','en'),(405,'Software::Translation',24,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Tails\ndescription: The Amnesic Incognito Live System or Tails is a Linux distribution aimed\n  at preserving privacy and anonymity. It is the next iteration of development on\n  the Incognito Linux distribution. It is based on Debian, with all outgoing connections\n  forced to go through Tor. The system is designed to be booted as a live CD or USB\n  and no trace is left on local storage unless explicitly told to.\nurl: https://tails.boum.org/\nsource_url: https://tails.boum.org/contribute/git/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://tails.boum.org/doc/about/license/index.en.html\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Amnesic_Incognito_Live_System\nid: 23\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 12:04:13.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 12:11:08.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: tails.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 15489\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-25 12:11:07.000000000 Z\n','2013-10-29 13:50:03','en'),(406,'Software::Translation',24,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 24\nsoftware_id: 23\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 12:04:13.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 12:11:08.000000000 Z\ntitle: Tails\ndescription: The Amnesic Incognito Live System or Tails is a Linux distribution aimed\n  at preserving privacy and anonymity. It is the next iteration of development on\n  the Incognito Linux distribution. It is based on Debian, with all outgoing connections\n  forced to go through Tor. The system is designed to be booted as a live CD or USB\n  and no trace is left on local storage unless explicitly told to.\nurl: https://tails.boum.org/\nsource_url: https://tails.boum.org/contribute/git/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://tails.boum.org/doc/about/license/index.en.html\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Amnesic_Incognito_Live_System\n','2013-10-29 13:50:03','en'),(407,'Software::Translation',25,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: JonDo Live CD\ndescription: \'Jondo Live-CD/DVD offers a secure, pre-configured environment for anonymous\n  surfing and more. It is based on Debian GNU/Linux. The live system contains proxy\n  clients for JonDonym, Tor Onion Router and Mixmaster remailer. JonDoBrowser is pre-configured\n  for anonymous web surfing and TorBrowser is installed too. Thunderbird for e-mails,\n  Pidgin for anonymous instant messaging and chats, Parole media player, MAT for cleaning\n  documents and more application are part of the live-cd. The DVD version contains\n  additional software: LibreOffice.org, GIMP, Wuala, Calibre for eBooks and some other\n  tools.\'\nurl: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/en/jondo-live-cd.html\nsource_url: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/wiki/index.php/JonDo_sources\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/en/help/credits.html\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Anon_Proxy\nid: 24\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 13:20:37.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 13:20:37.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: jondonym.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 80701\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-25 13:20:37.000000000 Z\n','2013-10-29 13:50:05','en'),(408,'Software::Translation',25,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 25\nsoftware_id: 24\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 13:20:37.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 13:20:37.000000000 Z\ntitle: JonDo Live CD\ndescription: \'Jondo Live-CD/DVD offers a secure, pre-configured environment for anonymous\n  surfing and more. It is based on Debian GNU/Linux. The live system contains proxy\n  clients for JonDonym, Tor Onion Router and Mixmaster remailer. JonDoBrowser is pre-configured\n  for anonymous web surfing and TorBrowser is installed too. Thunderbird for e-mails,\n  Pidgin for anonymous instant messaging and chats, Parole media player, MAT for cleaning\n  documents and more application are part of the live-cd. The DVD version contains\n  additional software: LibreOffice.org, GIMP, Wuala, Calibre for eBooks and some other\n  tools.\'\nurl: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/en/jondo-live-cd.html\nsource_url: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/wiki/index.php/JonDo_sources\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://anonymous-proxy-servers.net/en/help/credits.html\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Anon_Proxy\n','2013-10-29 13:50:05','en'),(409,'Software::Translation',26,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Whonix\ndescription: \"Whonix is an operating system focused on anonymity, privacy and security.\n  It\'s based on the Tor anonymity network, Debian GNU/Linux and security by isolation.\n  DNS leaks are impossible, and not even malware with root privileges can find out\n  the user\'s real IP.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhonix consists of two parts: One solely runs Tor and\n  acts as a gateway, which we call Whonix-Gateway. The other, which we call Whonix-Workstation,\n  is on a completely isolated network. Only connections through Tor are possible. \"\nurl: https://www.whonix.org/\nsource_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/blob/master/GPLv3\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whonix#Whonix_.28Anonymous_Operating_System.29\nid: 25\ncreated_at: 2013-10-26 02:32:06.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-26 02:36:54.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: whonix.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 154373\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-26 02:36:53.000000000 Z\n','2013-10-29 13:50:08','en'),(410,'Software::Translation',26,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 26\nsoftware_id: 25\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-26 02:32:06.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-26 02:32:06.000000000 Z\ntitle: Whonix\ndescription: \"Whonix is an operating system focused on anonymity, privacy and security.\n  It\'s based on the Tor anonymity network, Debian GNU/Linux and security by isolation.\n  DNS leaks are impossible, and not even malware with root privileges can find out\n  the user\'s real IP.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhonix consists of two parts: One solely runs Tor and\n  acts as a gateway, which we call Whonix-Gateway. The other, which we call Whonix-Workstation,\n  is on a completely isolated network. Only connections through Tor are possible. \"\nurl: https://www.whonix.org/\nsource_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/blob/master/GPLv3\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whonix#Whonix_.28Anonymous_Operating_System.29\n','2013-10-29 13:50:08','en'),(411,'Software::Translation',27,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: CyanogenMod\ndescription: CyanogenMod is an open source replacement distribution for smartphones\n  and tablet computers based on the Android mobile operating system. It is developed\n  as free and open source software based on the official releases of Android by Google,\n  with added original and third-party code.\nurl: http://www.cyanogenmod.org/\nsource_url: https://github.com/CyanogenMod\nprivacy_url: http://www.cyanogenmod.org/docs/privacy\ntos_url: http://www.cyanogenmod.org/docs/terms\nlicense_url: https://source.android.com/source/licenses.html\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CyanogenMod\nid: 26\ncreated_at: 2013-10-29 07:57:30.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-29 08:00:37.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: cyanogenmod.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 21782\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-29 08:00:36.000000000 Z\n','2013-10-29 13:50:10','en'),(412