ult to unencrypted\n  HTTP, or fill encrypted pages with links that go back to the unencrypted site. The\n  HTTPS Everywhere extension fixes these problems by using a clever technology to\n  rewrite requests to these sites to HTTPS.\"\nurl: https://www.eff.org/https-everywhere\nsource_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/https-everywhere.git\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/https-everywhere.git/blob_plain/HEAD:/LICENSE.txt\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\nid: 34\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:20:05.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:21:03.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: https-everywhere.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 117300\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-11-01 06:20:05.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-01 06:22:19','en'),(553,'Software::Translation',37,'create',NULL,NULL,'2013-11-01 06:27:11','en'),(554,'Software::Translation',37,'create',NULL,NULL,'2013-11-01 06:27:11','en'),(555,'Software::Translation',37,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Adblock Edge\ndescription: \nurl: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/adblock-edge/\nsource_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/src/a7aaa868e017c1cd35b400813319d2084da3d418/LICENSE?at=default\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\nid: 35\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:11.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:11.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: adblock-edge.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 3697\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:10.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-01 06:27:30','en'),(556,'Software::Translation',37,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 37\nsoftware_id: 35\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:11.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:11.000000000 Z\ntitle: Adblock Edge\ndescription: \nurl: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/adblock-edge/\nsource_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/src/a7aaa868e017c1cd35b400813319d2084da3d418/LICENSE?at=default\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\n','2013-11-01 06:27:30','en'),(557,'Software::Translation',37,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Adblock Edge\ndescription: \"\\r\\nAdblock Edge is a fork of the Adblock Plus version 2.1.2 extension\n  for blocking advertisements on the web. This fork will provide the same features\n  as Adblock Plus 2.X and higher but without \\\"acceptable ads\\\" feature. Adblock Edge\n  was primarily branched off from Adblock Plus 2.1.2 source code package \\\"http://adblockplus.org/downloads/adblockplus-2.1.2-source.tgz\\\"\n  created by Wladimir Palant.\"\nurl: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/adblock-edge/\nsource_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://bitbucket.org/adstomper/adblockedge/src/a7aaa868e017c1cd35b400813319d2084da3d418/LICENSE?at=default\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\nid: 35\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:11.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:30.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: adblock-edge.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 3697\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-11-01 06:27:10.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-01 06:28:27','en'),(558,'Software::Translation',38,'create',NULL,NULL,'2013-11-01 06:50:15','en'),(559,'Software::Translation',38,'create',NULL,NULL,'2013-11-01 06:50:15','en'),(560,'Software::Translation',38,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Disconnect\ndescription: \nurl: https://www.disconnect.me/disconnect\nsource_url: https://github.com/disconnectme/disconnect\nprivacy_url: https://disconnect.me/privacy\ntos_url: https://disconnect.me/terms\nlicense_url: https://github.com/disconnectme/disconnect/blob/master/README.markdown\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\nid: 36\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:50:15.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:50:15.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: \nlogo_content_type: \nlogo_file_size: \nlogo_updated_at: \n','2013-11-01 07:09:18','en'),(561,'Software::Translation',38,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 38\nsoftware_id: 36\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-11-01 06:50:15.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 06:50:15.000000000 Z\ntitle: Disconnect\ndescription: \nurl: https://www.disconnect.me/disconnect\nsource_url: https://github.com/disconnectme/disconnect\nprivacy_url: https://disconnect.me/privacy\ntos_url: https://disconnect.me/terms\nlicense_url: https://github.com/disconnectme/disconnect/blob/master/README.markdown\nwikipedia_url: \'\'\n','2013-11-01 07:09:18','en'),(562,'Software::Translation',2,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Tor Browser Bundle\ndescription: |\n  Tor (originally TOR, an acronym for The Onion Router, a usage now abandoned) is free software for enabling online anonymity. Tor directs Internet traffic through a free, worldwide, volunteer network consisting of more than four thousand relays to conceal a user\'s location or usage from anyone conducting network surveillance or traffic analysis. Using Tor makes it more difficult to trace Internet activity, including \"visits to Web sites, online posts, instant messages, and other communication forms\", back to the user and is intended to protect the personal privacy of users, as well as their freedom and ability to conduct confidential business by keeping their internet activities from being monitored.\nurl: https://www.torproject.org/projects/torbrowser.html.en\nsource_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git\nprivacy_url: https://www.torproject.org/about/overview.html.en\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git?a=blob_plain;hb=HEAD;f=LICENSE\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor_%28anonymity_network%29\nnotes: \nid: 2\ncreated_at: 2013-10-07 08:15:57.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-29 13:49:38.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: tor-browser-bundle.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 159151\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-25 03:02:00.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-02 11:37:49','en'),(563,'Software::Translation',2,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 2\nsoftware_id: 2\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-07 08:15:57.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-29 13:49:38.000000000 Z\ntitle: Tor Browser Bundle\ndescription: |\n  Tor (originally TOR, an acronym for The Onion Router, a usage now abandoned) is free software for enabling online anonymity. Tor directs Internet traffic through a free, worldwide, volunteer network consisting of more than four thousand relays to conceal a user\'s location or usage from anyone conducting network surveillance or traffic analysis. Using Tor makes it more difficult to trace Internet activity, including \"visits to Web sites, online posts, instant messages, and other communication forms\", back to the user and is intended to protect the personal privacy of users, as well as their freedom and ability to conduct confidential business by keeping their internet activities from being monitored.\nurl: https://www.torproject.org/projects/torbrowser.html.en\nsource_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git\nprivacy_url: https://www.torproject.org/about/overview.html.en\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git?a=blob_plain;hb=HEAD;f=LICENSE\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor_%28anonymity_network%29\nnotes: \n','2013-11-02 11:37:49','en'),(564,'Category::Translation',7,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Web Browsers\ndescription: \"Try to use <strong>Tor Browser Bundle</strong> (TBB) for all of your\n  web surfing. It will offer you far better anonymity than any other browser. Make\n  sure to [learn the basics of Tor](https://www.torproject.org/docs/faq.html.en) before\n  using it. If the site you want to visit will not work in the TBB, try Firefox instead,\n  but realize that it does not anonymize your IP by default.\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TBB notes:\n  Using the TBB to sign into websites that contain your real ID is counterproductive,\n  and may trip the site\'s fraud protection. Make sure to check for HTTPS before signing\n  in to a website through Tor. Signing into HTTP websites can result in your ID being\n  captured by a Tor exit node.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Firefox</strong> notes: This\n  browser uses Google search by default: replace it with a more <a href=\'#web-search\'>private\n  alternative</a>. Another debranded alternative to Firefox is <a href=\'http://www.geticeweasel.org/\'>Iceweasel</a>,\n  a browser for Debian-based distributions.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Why are Chromium, SRWare\n  Iron, et al. not recommended on PRISM Break? <a href=\'https://github.com/nylira/prism-break/issues/169\'>More\n  info here.</a></p>\"\nid: 7\ncreated_at: 2013-10-06 11:30:26.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 03:34:26.000000000 Z\nparent_id: 1\nsort_order: \n','2013-11-02 11:49:19','en'),(565,'Category::Translation',7,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 7\ncategory_id: 7\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-06 13:11:51.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-01 03:34:26.000000000 Z\ntitle: Web Browsers\ndescription: \"Try to use <strong>Tor Browser Bundle</strong> (TBB) for all of your\n  web surfing. It will offer you far better anonymity than any other browser. Make\n  sure to [learn the basics of Tor](https://www.torproject.org/docs/faq.html.en) before\n  using it. If the site you want to visit will not work in the TBB, try Firefox instead,\n  but realize that it does not anonymize your IP by default.\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TBB notes:\n  Using the TBB to sign into websites that contain your real ID is counterproductive,\n  and may trip the site\'s fraud protection. Make sure to check for HTTPS before signing\n  in to a website through Tor. Signing into HTTP websites can result in your ID being\n  captured by a Tor exit node.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Firefox</strong> notes: This\n  browser uses Google search by default: replace it with a more <a href=\'#web-search\'>private\n  alternative</a>. Another debranded alternative to Firefox is <a href=\'http://www.geticeweasel.org/\'>Iceweasel</a>,\n  a browser for Debian-based distributions.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Why are Chromium, SRWare\n  Iron, et al. not recommended on PRISM Break? <a href=\'https://github.com/nylira/prism-break/issues/169\'>More\n  info here.</a></p>\"\n','2013-11-02 11:49:19','en'),(566,'Software::Translation',2,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Tor Browser Bundle\ndescription: |\n  Tor (originally TOR, an acronym for The Onion Router, a usage now abandoned) is free software for enabling online anonymity. Tor directs Internet traffic through a free, worldwide, volunteer network consisting of more than four thousand relays to conceal a user\'s location or usage from anyone conducting network surveillance or traffic analysis. Using Tor makes it more difficult to trace Internet activity, including \"visits to Web sites, online posts, instant messages, and other communication forms\", back to the user and is intended to protect the personal privacy of users, as well as their freedom and ability to conduct confidential business by keeping their internet activities from being monitored.\nurl: https://www.torproject.org/projects/torbrowser.html.en\nsource_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git\nprivacy_url: https://www.torproject.org/about/overview.html.en\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git?a=blob_plain;hb=HEAD;f=LICENSE\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor_%28anonymity_network%29\nnotes: Using the TBB to sign into websites that contain your real ID is counterproductive,\n  and may trip the site\'s fraud protection. Make sure to check for HTTPS before signing\n  in to a website through Tor. Signing into HTTP websites can result in your ID being\n  captured by a Tor exit node.\nid: 2\ncreated_at: 2013-10-07 08:15:57.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-02 11:37:49.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: tor-browser-bundle.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 159151\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-25 03:02:00.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-02 11:50:30','en'),(567,'Software::Translation',2,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 2\nsoftware_id: 2\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-07 08:15:57.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-11-02 11:37:49.000000000 Z\ntitle: Tor Browser Bundle\ndescription: |\n  Tor (originally TOR, an acronym for The Onion Router, a usage now abandoned) is free software for enabling online anonymity. Tor directs Internet traffic through a free, worldwide, volunteer network consisting of more than four thousand relays to conceal a user\'s location or usage from anyone conducting network surveillance or traffic analysis. Using Tor makes it more difficult to trace Internet activity, including \"visits to Web sites, online posts, instant messages, and other communication forms\", back to the user and is intended to protect the personal privacy of users, as well as their freedom and ability to conduct confidential business by keeping their internet activities from being monitored.\nurl: https://www.torproject.org/projects/torbrowser.html.en\nsource_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git\nprivacy_url: https://www.torproject.org/about/overview.html.en\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor.git?a=blob_plain;hb=HEAD;f=LICENSE\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor_%28anonymity_network%29\nnotes: Using the TBB to sign into websites that contain your real ID is counterproductive,\n  and may trip the site\'s fraud protection. Make sure to check for HTTPS before signing\n  in to a website through Tor. Signing into HTTP websites can result in your ID being\n  captured by a Tor exit node.\n','2013-11-02 11:50:30','en'),(568,'Category::Translation',44,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Operating Systems (Live)\ndescription: \nid: 40\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 09:58:49.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 10:00:07.000000000 Z\nparent_id: 1\nsort_order: \n','2013-11-02 11:58:30','en'),(569,'Category::Translation',44,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 44\ncategory_id: 40\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 09:58:49.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-25 09:58:49.000000000 Z\ntitle: Operating Systems (Live)\ndescription: \n','2013-11-02 11:58:30','en'),(570,'Software::Translation',26,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Whonix\ndescription: Whonix is an anonymous general purpose operating system based on VirtualBox,\n  Debian GNU/Linux and Tor. By Whonix design, IP and DNS leaks are impossible. Not\n  even Malware as Superuser can find out the user\'s real IP address/location.\nurl: https://www.whonix.org/\nsource_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/blob/master/GPLv3\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whonix\nnotes: \nid: 25\ncreated_at: 2013-10-26 02:32:06.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-29 14:03:59.000000000 Z\nlogo_file_name: whonix.png\nlogo_content_type: image/png\nlogo_file_size: 154373\nlogo_updated_at: 2013-10-26 02:36:53.000000000 Z\n','2013-11-02 11:59:56','en'),(571,'Software::Translation',26,'update',NULL,'---\nid: 26\nsoftware_id: 25\nlocale: en\ncreated_at: 2013-10-26 02:32:06.000000000 Z\nupdated_at: 2013-10-29 14:03:59.000000000 Z\ntitle: Whonix\ndescription: Whonix is an anonymous general purpose operating system based on VirtualBox,\n  Debian GNU/Linux and Tor. By Whonix design, IP and DNS leaks are impossible. Not\n  even Malware as Superuser can find out the user\'s real IP address/location.\nurl: https://www.whonix.org/\nsource_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/\nprivacy_url: \'\'\ntos_url: \'\'\nlicense_url: https://github.com/Whonix/Whonix/blob/master/GPLv3\nwikipedia_url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whonix\nnotes: \n','2013-11-02 11:59:56','en'),(572,'Category::Translation',44,'update',NULL,'---\ntitle: Operating Systems (Live)\ndescription: \'  \"i18n-live-cd-notes\": \"<p>A live distribution like <strong>Tails</strong>\n  or <strong>Liberté Linux</strong> is the fastest and easiest way to a secure operating\n  system. All you have to do is create a bootable CD or USB drive with the files provided\n  and you&rsquo;re set. Everything else will be preconfigured for you.</p>\'\nid: 40\ncreated_at: 2013-10-25 09